  "prompt": "What is the best comeback when someone says \"Been there, done that\"?",
  "response": "A good comeback to \"Been there, done that\" can be lighthearted, confident, or clever, depending on the tone of the conversation. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Playful:**  \n   \"Not like *this*, you haven't.\"\n\n2. **Confident:**  \n   \"Then you already know it\u2019s worth doing again.\"\n\n3. **Curious:**  \n   \"Oh, cool! What did you learn from it?\"\n\n4. **Challenging:**  \n   \"Been there? Great. Let\u2019s see if you can keep up.\"\n\n5. **Witty:**  \n   \"Yeah, but did you get the t-shirt?\"\n\n6. **Encouraging:**  \n   \"Perfect, then you can show me how it\u2019s done.\"\n\nThe best approach depends on the context and your relationship with the person. Keep it fun or constructive to keep the conversation positive!",
